SIMPLE: rote
RECORDS: 6

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rote
<hw>Rote</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A root.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rote</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rote
<hw>Rote</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>rote</ets>,
probably of German origin; cf. MHG. <ets>rotte</ets>, OHG.
<ets>rota</ets>, <ets>hrota</ets>, LL. <ets>chrotta</ets>. Cf.
<er>Crowd</er> a kind of violin.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A kind of
guitar, the notes of which were produced by a small wheel or wheel-like
arrangement; an instrument similar to the hurdy-gurdy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Well could he sing and play on a <qex>rote</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>extracting mistuned dirges from their harps, crowds, and
<qex>rotes</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rote</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Rote
<hw>Rote</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Rut</er> roaring.]</ety>
<def>The noise produced by the surf of the sea dashing upon the shore.
See <er>Rut</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rote</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Rote
<hw>Rote</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>rote</ets>, F.
<ets>route</ets>, road, path. See <er>Route</er>, and cf. <er>Rut</er> a
furrow, <er>Routine</er>.]</ety> <def>A frequent repetition of forms of
speech without attention to the meaning; mere repetition; <as>as, to
learn rules by <ex>rote</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>till he the first verse could [<it>i. e.</it>, knew] all by
<qex>rote</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy love did read by <qex>rote</qex>, and could not spell.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rote</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Rote
<hw>Rote</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Roted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Roting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To learn or repeat by rote.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rote</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 6 ====
HEADWORD: Rote
<hw>Rote</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To go out by rotation or
succession; to rotate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <-- = rotate out? -->
<rj><au>Z. Grey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rotella</ent>⟦br⟧
